      • findLabelAtIndex

        public static com.kms.katalon.core.testobject.TestObject findLabelAtIndex​(java.lang.String testObjectName,
                                                                          int index)
        Find a Label at a given index from a list of similar Labels on the screen.

        There must already exist a TestObject in the "Labels" Object Repository that will serve as a template.

        For iOS, the TestObject should have the "type" property of "XCUIElementTypeStaticText" and the "name" property that matches the accessibility id of the collection of labels.

        For Android, the TestObject should have a "class" property that ends in "TextView" and a "resource-id" property that contains the resource-id shared by the collection of labels.

        Parameters:
        testObjectName - the name of the Label in the Object Repository which will be used as the template for finding all of the labels with the same class/type and accessibility/resource id.
        index - the place of the element in the list that you want to return. The first element is at index 1.
        Returns:
        the matching Label TestObject

        Returns:

      • findLabelWithText

        public static com.kms.katalon.core.testobject.TestObject findLabelWithText​(java.lang.String testObjectName,
                                                                           java.lang.String labelText)
                                                                    throws ListItemsNotFoundException
        Find a Label with given text from a list of similar Labels on the screen.

        There must already exist a TestObject in the "Labels" Object Repository that will serve as a template.

        For iOS, the TestObject should have the "type" property of "XCUIElementTypeStaticText" and the "name" property that matches the accessibility id of the collection of labels.

        For Android, the TestObject should have a "class" property that ends in "TextView" and a "resource-id" property that contains the resource-id shared by the collection of labels.

        Parameters:
        testObjectName - the name of the Label in the Object Repository which will be used as the template for finding all of the labels with the same class/type and accessibility/resource id.
        labelText - the text of the label to find. Must match exactly, including upper/lower case matching.
        Returns:
        the matching Label TestObject
        Throws:
        ListItemsNotFoundException - if the label isn't found.

      • findLabelWithText

        public static com.kms.katalon.core.testobject.TestObject findLabelWithText​(java.lang.String testObjectName,
                                                                           java.lang.String labelText,
                                                                           com.kms.katalon.core.model.FailureHandling failureHandling)
                                                                    throws ListItemsNotFoundException
        Find a Label with given text from a list of similar Labels on the screen.

        There must already exist a TestObject in the "Labels" Object Repository that will serve as a template.

        For iOS, the TestObject should have the "type" property of "XCUIElementTypeStaticText" and the "name" property that matches the accessibility id of the collection of labels.

        For Android, the TestObject should have a "class" property that ends in "TextView" and a "resource-id" property that contains the resource-id shared by the collection of labels.

        Parameters:
        testObjectName - the name of the Label in the Object Repository which will be used as the template for finding all of the labels with the same class/type and accessibility/resource id.
        labelText - the text of the label to find. Must match exactly, including upper/lower case matching.
        failureHandling - how the test flow should be handled in the event that the label can't be found.
        Returns:
        the matching Label TestObject
        Throws:
        ListItemsNotFoundException - if the label isn't found, unless the failureHandling is CONTINUE_ON_FAILURE or OPTIONAL.
